get_array(prefix, iter_list, sufix, unit)[source]¶

Generates a np.array of values with analog type strings like ch_1001_before … ch_1030_before.

In this example ch_ would be the prefix, [1001, ..., 1030] is the iter_list and _before is the sufix.

Note

Different Types are in different rows. Different measurement points are in different columns.

Parameters:
  • prefix – prefix of the type
  • iter_list (list) – list to iterate over
  • sufix (str) – sufix of the type
Returns:

array of arrays
Return type:

np.array
get_expression(val, unit, o=False)[source]¶

Gets an dict by means of get_object(), compares o.Unit with unit and returns sym.sympyfied Expression.

get_obj(val, unit)[source]¶

Abbreviation for the method get_object: searches an dict (o) by means of method get_object. Compares o.Unit with unit parameter and returns numpy typed values by means of method get_value.

Parameters:
  • val (str) – val value of the key Type to search for
  • unit (str) – unit expected unit of the returned result
Returns:

dict with Type, Value, Unit keys
Return type:

{Type: str, Unit: str, Value: np.array}
get_object(key, val, o=False, d=0)[source]¶

get_value(val, unit, o=False)[source]¶

class vpy.values.AuxValues(doc)[source]¶

Bases: vpy.document.Document

get_by_time(meastime, auxtime, timeunit, auxval, valunit)[source]¶

..todo:: write a better description

Some values are measured only a few times like offsets. Such values are stored below the AuxValues-section. This Function implements a expansion mechanism and returns a array of the length len(meastime)

Note

The first measured offset is valid until the second offset is measured.

Parameters:
  • meastime (np.array) – meastime array
  • auxtime (str) – auxtime name of the time type to expand
  • timeunit (str) – timeunit unit of the type to expand
  • auxval (str) – auxval name of the type to expand
  • valunit (str) – valunit unit of the type to expand
